That's my partner.

546
00:39:14,207 --> 00:39:16,562
You better be glad you don't have to
mess with him.

547
00:39:16,767 --> 00:39:19,235
That guy's into some crazy-ass shit.

548
00:39:19,447 --> 00:39:22,485
Now, either you can tell me
where you put the foot...

549
00:39:22,688 --> 00:39:25,998
...or you're gonna be dealing with
that crazy-ass motherfucker.

550
00:39:45,052 --> 00:39:48,601
Big Shirley by a nose!

551
00:39:51,013 --> 00:39:53,686
She won!

552
00:39:54,453 --> 00:39:58,367
Oh, God, I just can't believe it.
I won $ 16.

553
00:39:58,574 --> 00:39:59,893
I told you this would be fun.

554
00:40:00,174 --> 00:40:03,292
- How much did you win?
- I don't know.

555
00:40:03,495 --> 00:40:05,884
- Four thousand.
- Four thousand what?

556
00:40:06,095 --> 00:40:08,291
Dollars.

557
00:40:17,137 --> 00:40:22,690
And by the way, I had an affair
with a hairdresser last year.

558
00:40:24,298 --> 00:40:27,689
- You did?
- Yep.

559
00:40:39,781 --> 00:40:42,739
Are you a cup?
How many cups are you?

560
00:40:42,941 --> 00:40:46,093
I'm a loaf of bread.

561
00:40:47,262 --> 00:40:48,900
Hello?

562
00:40:49,102 --> 00:40:51,617
Okay. Talk slowly.

563
00:40:55,183 --> 00:40:57,982
I'm gonna see you in a few hours.

564
00:40:58,184 --> 00:41:01,494
Slow down. Slower.

565
00:41:01,704 --> 00:41:03,696
Well, you're gonna have to wait.

566
00:41:03,905 --> 00:41:07,454
- Because you have to.
- Brenda.

567
00:41:07,865 --> 00:41:12,144
Just stay there.
I'll call you in a half-hour.

568
00:41:12,346 --> 00:41:13,859
- Promise?
- I promise.

569
00:41:15,947 --> 00:41:19,826
- Who was that?
- Nothing to worry about.

570
00:41:20,988 --> 00:41:24,060
- I gotta go.
- Brenda, who was it?

571
00:41:25,748 --> 00:41:28,707
Just someone else, okay?
Just back off.

572
00:41:28,909 --> 00:41:33,267
I can't deal with this right now.
I'll call you.

573
00:41:40,271 --> 00:41:43,581
I'm glad you're staying in town.

574
00:41:49,992 --> 00:41:55,272
- He threw it out of his car?
- He was taking it to show some friends.

575
00:41:55,713 --> 00:41:57,511
Then it hit him,
he might get in trouble.

576
00:41:57,714 --> 00:42:00,706
What with people not supposed to
be in possession of others' feet.

577
00:42:00,914 --> 00:42:03,349
- He tossed it out.
- I've gotta get home.

578
00:42:03,555 --> 00:42:05,750
Just drop me off, and I'll
pick up my car later.

579
00:42:05,955 --> 00:42:08,834
All right, I'll take a look
where he said he tossed it.

580
00:42:09,036 --> 00:42:12,995
- You don't have to do that.
- Hey, how can I sleep?

581
00:42:13,196 --> 00:42:15,267
Knowing that there's
a foot on the loose?

582
00:42:15,557 --> 00:42:20,153
- You lost $25,000? It's just gone?
- I suppose it still exists.

583
00:42:20,357 --> 00:42:22,474
It's just not mine anymore.

584
00:42:23,358 --> 00:42:27,034
- I'm waiting for an explanation.
- Don't talk to me like a child.

585
00:42:27,239 --> 00:42:28,433
I was on a...

586
00:42:28,639 --> 00:42:30,357
What do you call it? A roll.

587
00:42:30,559 --> 00:42:33,597
So I kept betting more and more,
and I just felt so good...

588
00:42:33,800 --> 00:42:37,713
...like I was living someone else's life.
I was up $9000!

589
00:42:37,920 --> 00:42:40,196
And then I started to lose.

590
00:42:40,401 --> 00:42:44,792
And then I started to feel like me again,
and so I kept betting more and more...

591
00:42:45,002 --> 00:42:47,835
...and losing more and more.
- You should've been more careful.

592
00:42:48,042 --> 00:42:51,160
I don't want to be careful.
I want to feel alive.

593
00:42:51,363 --> 00:42:54,355
There should be a way to do that
that's a little less expensive.

594
00:42:54,683 --> 00:42:57,118
I have a right to make mistakes, Nate!

595
00:42:57,324 --> 00:42:59,713
You of all people shouldn't
begrudge me that.

596
00:43:05,805 --> 00:43:06,999
What?

597
00:43:08,885 --> 00:43:14,677
I lost $25,000. Okay, you got it
out of me. Now leave me alone!

598
00:43:36,210 --> 00:43:38,166
Hey.

599
00:43:39,050 --> 00:43:41,042
Claire?

600
00:43:41,891 --> 00:43:44,121
- You're David's friend.
- Keith.

601
00:43:46,372 --> 00:43:47,725
What's going on?

602
00:43:50,772 --> 00:43:53,162
Not much.

603
00:43:57,093 --> 00:43:58,652
So where's Claire now?

604
00:44:00,054 --> 00:44:05,413
I gotta say I'm totally relieved.
That I didn't lose it.

605
00:44:06,295 --> 00:44:08,251
Hey.

606
00:44:14,456 --> 00:44:17,017
Nice job, Rico.

607
00:44:17,737 --> 00:44:21,173
- Thank you.
- Boy, they did do a marvelous job.

608
00:44:22,018 --> 00:44:24,327
They ought to, they charged a fortune.

609
00:44:32,499 --> 00:44:34,889
Can I assist you, Miss Romano?

610
00:44:35,100 --> 00:44:36,453
I know it's silly...

611
00:44:36,660 --> 00:44:40,734
...but I just wanted to see with my own
eyes that Pop's all put together right.

612
00:44:40,941 --> 00:44:42,977
We get to do that, don't we?

613
00:44:53,303 --> 00:44:55,942
Okay. Good.

614
00:45:04,105 --> 00:45:06,824
I think I'll be able
to sleep much better now.

615
00:45:17,627 --> 00:45:21,540
- Rico, you gave him a foot?
- Yeah. Yeah.

616
00:45:21,748 --> 00:45:23,625
I thought it was for the best.

617
00:45:23,828 --> 00:45:26,023
Remember that leg of lamb
that your mother had...

618
00:45:26,228 --> 00:45:28,743
...in the back of her freezer for forever?
- Okay, stop.

619
00:45:28,949 --> 00:45:31,747
Embalmed, wrapped in latex
and duct tape.

620
00:45:32,469 --> 00:45:36,543
I was following him home
to get it back when I saw him toss it.

621
00:45:36,750 --> 00:45:39,218
Now I've been here for
hours, and I can't find it.

622
00:45:39,430 --> 00:45:42,423
- Describe it to me again.
- It's a foot.

623
00:45:42,631 --> 00:45:45,225
Why did you take it in the first place?

624
00:45:45,431 --> 00:45:48,902
Well, at the time, it seemed like a good
way to pay him back for something.

625
00:45:49,112 --> 00:45:51,467
I just wanted to shake him up.

626
00:45:51,672 --> 00:45:55,382
I don't understand how guys
can be so unshakable.

627
00:45:55,953 --> 00:45:58,229
I know what you mean.

628
00:45:59,994 --> 00:46:02,827
Did you ever suck a guy's toe?

629
00:46:06,235 --> 00:46:08,271
Yeah.

630
00:46:09,956 --> 00:46:12,106
Me too.

631
00:46:15,116 --> 00:46:18,473
Have you been
watching Mrs. Romano?

632
00:46:19,037 --> 00:46:20,755
Yeah.

633
00:46:20,957 --> 00:46:23,233
Been watching her all night.

634
00:46:23,438 --> 00:46:25,269
Are you thinking what I'm thinking?

635
00:46:25,478 --> 00:46:28,232
Casket climber.

636
00:46:28,719 --> 00:46:31,631
Her? She doesn't look that energetic.

637
00:46:31,919 --> 00:46:35,595
Yeah. Those are the ones
that really go for it.

638
00:46:37,280 --> 00:46:39,669
So we should probably have
a conversation with Rico...

639
00:46:39,880 --> 00:46:42,031
...about what's going on with Kroehner.

640
00:46:43,441 --> 00:46:45,557
Okay.

641
00:46:46,122 --> 00:46:49,751
So there was no baby christening
the other day. I lied.

642
00:46:50,762 --> 00:46:52,833
But I only took one
meeting with Gilardi.

643
00:46:53,043 --> 00:46:57,195
- You met with him? Why?
- Hey, Gilardi called me, okay?

644
00:46:57,403 --> 00:46:59,713
I have the right to consider my options.

645
00:47:00,004 --> 00:47:02,279
My father put you
through mortuary school.

646
00:47:05,125 --> 00:47:09,323
- I wanna go with you!
- Mrs. Romano! Mrs. Romano!

647
00:47:09,525 --> 00:47:10,595
- It's okay.
- Mommy!

648
00:47:10,806 --> 00:47:13,559
Grab her legs! It's okay.
It's okay. Here we go.

649
00:47:13,766 --> 00:47:15,518
- Here we go, Mrs. Romano.
- I'm sorry.

650
00:47:22,047 --> 00:47:24,243
I give up.

651
00:47:26,088 --> 00:47:28,444
It's not here.

652
00:47:31,129 --> 00:47:33,802
This probably isn't over.

653
00:47:35,330 --> 00:47:41,201
If there's a lesson to be learned, it's
that your actions have consequences.

654
00:47:41,411 --> 00:47:44,209
Yeah, well, Gabe should learn that.

655
00:47:48,852 --> 00:47:52,003
I know you and my brother are,
like...

656
00:47:52,613 --> 00:47:54,365
...gay.

657
00:47:57,053 --> 00:47:59,090
Okay.

658
00:48:02,654 --> 00:48:04,452
What do you see in him?

659
00:48:05,695 --> 00:48:11,293
- He's just David, you know?
- I know. That's why I'm asking.

660
00:48:12,416 --> 00:48:16,615
He is smart. He's kind. He's funny.

661
00:48:18,217 --> 00:48:21,926
I know he can be a little uptight,
but underneath that, he's...

662
00:48:23,818 --> 00:48:27,493
...such a little boy. Innocent.

663
00:48:27,698 --> 00:48:28,734
And I like that.

664
00:48:30,299 --> 00:48:33,416
Most of the men I meet, well...

665
00:48:33,619 --> 00:48:35,975
...they kind of just want me
to be one thing.

666
00:48:36,260 --> 00:48:38,490
What, like, big, black sex cop?

667
00:48:38,700 --> 00:48:42,091
"Sorry I was speeding, officer, I guess
you'll have to punish me now."

668
00:48:42,381 --> 00:48:43,700
Yeah.

669
00:48:43,901 --> 00:48:48,498
And I don't want to be that.
Rent a video.

670
00:48:48,742 --> 00:48:50,300
David...

671
00:48:50,742 --> 00:48:52,973
...he gets me.

672
00:48:53,743 --> 00:48:58,659
When someone sees you as you
really are and wants to be with you...

673
00:48:59,024 --> 00:49:01,538
...that's powerful.

674
00:49:05,985 --> 00:49:08,180
Whatever.

675
00:49:09,865 --> 00:49:13,063
I wish I could know
the David you know.

676
00:49:13,826 --> 00:49:16,260
You could be a little nicer to him.

677
00:49:16,546 --> 00:49:18,458
He's under a lot of stress...

678
00:49:18,667 --> 00:49:21,306
...with that cremation place
opening across the street.

679
00:49:22,107 --> 00:49:25,225
What cremation place?

680
00:49:25,508 --> 00:49:27,544
She stole a foot?

681
00:49:27,748 --> 00:49:29,341
From a person?

682
00:49:29,549 --> 00:49:33,098
Yes. Would it have been better
if it was an animal's?

683
00:49:33,309 --> 00:49:34,378
