684
00:49:34,589 --> 00:49:38,026
You wake up one day
and your baby's stolen a foot.

685
00:49:38,230 --> 00:49:41,780
- Where have I been?
- Losing $25,000.

686
00:49:45,631 --> 00:49:47,623
Hey.

687
00:49:53,433 --> 00:49:55,947
Okay, I've had a long day.

688
00:49:56,473 --> 00:49:59,750
Oh, David, I ran into your friend Keith.

689
00:50:00,154 --> 00:50:03,510
- Who's Keith?
- You met at Dad's thing.

690
00:50:03,714 --> 00:50:07,344
- I never met a Keith.
- Yes, you did, the cop.

691
00:50:07,555 --> 00:50:09,273
I asked him to help out.

692
00:50:09,475 --> 00:50:12,468
He'll see what he can do
about there not being an official report.

693
00:50:12,676 --> 00:50:15,190
Why does this person have to be
so involved in our life?

694
00:50:15,396 --> 00:50:18,787
Claire, we should probably talk about
getting you some help.

695
00:50:19,557 --> 00:50:21,548
You are not my father.

696
00:50:22,557 --> 00:50:25,948
If you need a project, get a dog.

697
00:50:27,078 --> 00:50:30,116
Keith says the school's probably
gonna make me see a shrink anyway.

698
00:50:30,319 --> 00:50:31,957
Oh, dear.

699
00:50:32,159 --> 00:50:34,195
By the way, that house
across the street?

700
00:50:35,120 --> 00:50:36,439
It's on fire.

701
00:50:58,803 --> 00:51:01,238
I guess this should solve
all your problems.

702
00:51:17,967 --> 00:51:20,276
Freckles!

703
00:51:22,047 --> 00:51:23,401
Freckles!

704
00:51:23,608 --> 00:51:25,644
Here, girl!

